      "discuss_url": "https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48542100",
      "score": 782,
      "comments": 375,
      "author": "cloudking",
      "published": "2026-06-15T14:46:53Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Practitioners pair Qwen-2.5-Coder or DeepSeek-Coder-V2 with Ollama and the Continue.dev IDE extension to replace proprietary LLMs for daily coding.",
        "Achieving viable tokens/second for 70B+ models requires high-end hardware like Apple Silicon Mac Studios (64GB+ unified memory) or dual RTX 3090/4090 GPUs.",
        "Local setups excel at offline, context-aware autocomplete and privacy, but struggle with complex, multi-file architectural reasoning compared to Claude 3.5 Sonnet."
      ]
    },
